solution.p:
\amp F - \mu_{k1}N_{1} - \mu_{k12}N_{12} = m_1 a_1 \amp N_1 - N_{12} - m_1 g = 0 \amp \mu_{k12}N_{12} = m_2 a_2 \amp N_{12} - m_2 g = 0
First we get N_{12} from the last equation. Then, we use it to get a_2 and N_1. Then we get a_1.
a_2 \amp = \frac{\mu_{k12}m_2 g}{ m_2} = \mu_{k12}g. a_1 \amp = \frac{F - \mu_{k1}N_{1} - \mu_{k12}N_{12}}{m_1} \amp = \frac{F - \mu_{k1}(m_1 + m_2)g - \mu_{k12}m_2 g}{m_1}
